  "text": "Investigation of the Interaction between ISCU(M108I) and Cysteine Desulfurase (NIA) [CITATION_1] . We used NMR spectroscopy to study the interaction between ISCU(M108I) and the cysteine desulfurase complex (NIA) [CITATION_2] Figure  5A,B) . The peaks that shifted or broadened the most correspond to residues G18, G30−A34, V40−L43, K59, F61−C63, S69, L72, N90, T91, and C98 ( Figure 5C ). The (NIA) 2 binding site on ISCU(M108I) revealed by chemical shift perturbations ( Figure 5D ) agrees well with the X-ray structure of (NIAU) [CITATION_3] . [CITATION_4] The interaction between ISCU-(M108I) and (NIA) 2 was further confirmed by size-exclusion chromatography (SEC) and sodium dodecyl sulfate−polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis (SDS−PAGE) ( Figure 5E,F) . The SEC profile of (NIAU(M108I)) [CITATION_5] was similar to that of (NIAU) 2 ( Figure 5E ). ITC was used to quantify the interaction between ISCU(M108I) and (NIA) [CITATION_6] . Titration of (NIA) [CITATION_7] with ISCU(M108I) resulted in an endothermic reaction that was fitted to a 1:1 binding model with a K d of 2.6 ± 0.6 μM (Figure Biochemistry Article 5G). The binding constant is similar to that of (NIA) [CITATION_8] and ISCU (K d = 1.7 ± 0.4 μM).",
